SIMPLE: serpentize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Serpentize
<hw>Ser"pent*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To turn or
bend like a serpent, first in one direction and then in the opposite; to
meander; to wind; to serpentine.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The river runs before the door, and <qex>serpentizes</qex> more
than you can conceive.</q> <rj><qau>Walpole.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serpentry</ent>⟦br⟧
